    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "BA AIM\nFOTo No. (MIAMI\n34103\nCARGO CLIPPER LIFTS OFF THE RUNWAY AT MIAMI\nOne of PAA's fleet of ten C-46-type cargo Clippers\nheads for Latin America from Miami. They operate on\nscheduled routes from Miami, New Orleans and Houston to\nCentral America, Mexico, the Caribbean and the north coast\nof South America. On their return trips, the Clippers can\ndrop in at any field that can accommodate a C-46 to pick up\nodd-lot cargoes or an entire Mipper-load of Latin American\nproducts-fruit, wood and leather handicraft, sisal, flowers,\ncoffee or minerals.\n#\n#\n#",
      "1948\nTEN WAR-TESTED CURTISS COMMANDOS (C-46s) WERE LEASED FROM THE U.S.\nAIR FORCE IN 1948 TO SERVE AS CARGO CLIPPERS IN LATIN AMERICA.\nEVENTUALLY THEY WERE REPLACED BY FOUR-ENGINED DC-4s."
    ],
